OL,5,Creview
OL,7,F"At the heart of the changes must be a
OL,8,Fnew relationship with women, families
OL,9,Fand communities, with an enabling
OL,10,Fenvironment for all staff and
OL,11,Fstudents, and better informed, better
OL,12,Fimplemented monitoring, commissioning
OL,13,Fand governance."
OL,15,FProf Renfrew added: "Many women and
OL,16,Ftheir partners who engaged with the
OL,17,Freview described a range of
OL,18,Funacceptable experiences during their
OL,19,Fmaternity journey which contributed to
OL,20,Fphysical and emotional harm, sometimes
OL,21,Fcausing long-lasting distress.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@PO]wD@UOU
