OL,5,Creview
OL,7,F"Many midwives and interdisciplinary
OL,8,Fcolleagues described working in
OL,9,Fcircumstances where they could not
OL,10,Fgive the quality of care that they
OL,11,Fknew was needed.
OL,13,F"The voices of the women and families
OL,14,Fand of the staff who spoke so openly,
OL,15,Foften at the cost of re-experiencing
OL,16,Ftheir trauma and harm, must result in
OL,17,Fthe outcome they all hope for ` a
OL,18,Fbetter experience for women, babies,
OL,19,Fand families in the future."
